turtles-shredders-revenge-review-185022231.html"><em>《碎纸机的复仇》</em></a>中，除了看和闻这个角色之外，你不会声称比你的朋友有优势。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>即使你自从伊士曼和莱尔德制作第一部漫画以来就是忍者神龟粉丝，也没有办法购买这些游戏手柄。相反，您必须关注 Xbox Game Pass<del>推特</del>X 并在 8 月 13 日之前转发<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/XboxGamePass/status/1683492348234199041">帖子</a>。如果你一定要操作一个披萨味的控制器，这些控制器将在 8 月 2 日的促销活动中在纽约第五大道的微软体验中心出现——但你最好只点一个馅饼，在关卡之间吃点东西。</p><p>是的，这与微软两年前推出的<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2021/10/11/xbox-unveils-xbox-series-x-consoles-celebrating-nickelodeon-all-star-brawl/">《忍者神龟》主题 Xbox Series X 的</a>营销策略不相上下。最终，你为派拉蒙做的事情比你自己做的还要多。不过，请这样看：与<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/i-tried-the-krispy-kreme-xbox-donut-163000967.html">Krispy Kreme Xbox 甜甜圈</a>不同，几周后你仍然可以向你的朋友展示一些东西。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/microsofts-latest-xbox-marketing-stunt-is-a-pizza-scented-controller-153724328.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/microsofts-latest-xbox-marketing-stunt-is-a-pizza-scented-controller-153724328.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7c8b0e8d-6a5d-4b3b-9c9d-f9e6738ac1bb</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 24 Jul 2023 15:37:24 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690213045</ingested><modified> 2023-07-24T15:37:31+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/8125d820-2a2d-11ee-9f7a-01122f7a3cf1" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/8125d820-2a2d-11ee-9f7a-01122f7a3cf1" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Pizza-scented 'TMNT: Mutant Mayhem' Xbox controller]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Pizza-scented 'TMNT: Mutant Mayhem' Xbox controller]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best E Ink tablets for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>我一生中的大部分时间都是一个笔记本人。多年来，我有几十本笔记本，它们可以作为待办事项列表、故事创意、会议笔记以及介于两者之间的所有内容的存储库。但在我成年生活的某个时刻，我放弃了实体笔记本，因为在手机上随时可以使用的各种应用程序中以数字方式保存所有这些东西变得更容易。我为了数字便利而牺牲了触觉满足，我的一小部分人为我留下的所有半满的笔记本感到哀悼。</p><p>对于像我这样的人来说，电子墨水平板电脑可能是解决那些决斗冲动的解决方案。它们可以将在普通笔记本上书写的感觉与数字化文档的许多便利结合起来。电子墨水平板电脑可以让您在一台设备上记下所有笔记，同时还可以让您像使用笔和纸一样使用手写笔进行书写。不过，与普通平板电脑和手写笔不同的是，电子墨水平板电脑远未普及，但游戏中的玩家数量足够多，因此决定购买哪一款比您想象的要复杂。我们测试了一些目前最流行的电子墨水平板电脑，看看它们的工作效果如何，它们到底有多方便，以及哪些是当今最好的。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2>电子墨水平板电脑值得购买吗？</h2><p>对于特定人群来说，电子墨水平板电脑是值得购买的。如果您更喜欢电子墨水显示屏的外观和感觉，而不是传统平板电脑上的液晶面板，那么它很有意义。对于那些想要更接近纸张的书写体验（尽管您可以在带有合适屏幕保护膜的普通平板电脑上获得这种体验）或整体上更不受干扰的设备的人来说，它们也是不错的选择。</p><p>最后一点是关键。大多数电子墨水平板电脑与普通平板电脑运行的操作系统不同，因此您的操作自然会受到限制。即使那些允许您下载 Chrome、Instagram 和 Facebook 等传统应用程序的平板电脑，E Ink 平板电脑也并非旨在为您提供最佳的休闲浏览体验。这主要是由于电子墨水显示屏的性质造成的，与最便宜的 iPad 上的面板相比，电子墨水显示屏具有明显的刷新效果、缺乏色彩且质量较低。</p><p>可以说，你<em>不想</em>使用 iPad（所有型号都支持手写笔输入、大量阅读应用程序等）的最大原因是因为它更容易被电子邮件、社交媒体和其他与互联网相关的诱惑分心。如果您属于这种情况，电子阅读器也值得考虑，但要知道大多数标准电子阅读器不接受手写笔输入。如果您喜欢在书籍的页边空白处做笔记、在 PDF 上添加下划线和标记等，那么电子阅读器就无法满足您的需求。</p><h2>在电子墨水平板电脑中寻找什么</h2><p>在测试过程中，我发现了四个主要因素可以真正决定您使用电子墨水平板电脑的体验：首先是写作体验。它的好坏很大程度上取决于显示器的刷新率（可以这么说，每次你把笔放在“纸上”后它会刷新吗？）和手写笔的延迟。大多数延迟几乎没有，但有些延迟比其他延迟更差。最后，您应该在购买之前仔细检查您喜欢的电子墨水平板电脑是否配备了手写笔。不管你相信与否，其中许多都要求您单独购买笔。</p><p>其次要考虑的是阅读体验。您会在这款平板电脑上阅读多少书籍、文档和其他内容？虽然您可以找到各种不同尺寸的电子墨水平板电脑，但大多数电子墨水平板电脑往往比标准电子阅读器更大，因为它使书写更加容易。拥有更大的显示屏并不是一件坏事，但它可能会让长时间握持它变得稍微不舒服。 （大多数电子阅读器的大小与平装书大致相同，给您与模拟阅读类似的感觉）。</p><p>支持的文件类型也会产生很大的差异。在这里很难做出一揽子声明，因为电子墨水平板电脑之间的差异很大。总而言之，如果您选择一家已经拥有电子书销售历史的公司（例如亚马逊或 Kobo）制作的书籍，您将获得更好的阅读体验。您通过 Kindle 或 Kobo 商店购买的所有图书都应自动在您的 Kindle 或 Kobo E Ink 平板电脑上可用。特别是对于 Kindle 图书，由于它们受 DRM 保护，因此尝试将<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.ebook-converter.com/104-how-to-read-kindle-ebook-kobo.htm">这些图书转移到第三方设备</a>不一定是最好的主意。除非平板电脑支持阅读应用程序，例如 Amazon 的 Kindle 或 Kobo 应用程序，否则您将仅限于支持的文件类型，例如 ePUB、PDF、MOBI、JPEG、PNG 等。</p><p>第三，大多数电子墨水平板电脑都具有一些搜索功能，但不同型号的功能差异很大。您需要考虑能够搜索所有手写笔记和标记对您来说有多重要。我注意到 Amazon 和 Kobo 的 E Ink 平板电脑可以轻松查阅书籍和文件中所做的笔记，因为它们会自动保存您记笔记、突出显示等内容的页面。在具有不同支持文件类型的电子墨水平板电脑上，搜索标准化程度较低，但其功能本身就非常强大。例如，我测试的一些设备支持手写笔记中的文本搜索以及手写识别，后者允许您将涂鸦翻译成键入的文本。</p><p>最后要考虑的因素是共享和连接。是的，我们确定电子墨水平板电脑可以成为很好的无干扰设备，但大多数制造商都明白您的笔记和涂鸦不是在真空中创建的。您可能希望在其他地方访问它们，这需要某种形式的连接。我尝试过的所有电子墨水平板电脑都是 WiFi 设备，有些支持云同步、配套移动应用程序以及通过电子邮件导出笔记的功能，以便您可以在其他地方访问它们。然而，它们都没有直接与 Evernote 或 OneNote 等数字笔记记录系统集成，因此如果您也使用此类应用程序，这些设备始终会起到一定的补充作用。最终，您应该考虑在平板电脑部分完成<em>后，</em>您将如何处理将在电子墨水平板电脑上与之交互的文档。</p><h2>最适合大多数人：reMarkable 2</h2><p><core-commerce id="6d40b6267af5444d8ef158783c2c83d6" data-type="product-list"></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://remarkable.com/store/remarkable-2">最新的 reMarkable 平板电脑</a>并未名列前茅，因为它是我们测试过的功能最齐全甚至最有趣的电子墨水平板电脑。相反，它提供了人们在此类设备中会发现有用的功能的最佳组合。我们将详细讨论它们，但首先值得一提的是构建质量。 reMarkable 2 的重量不到一磅，是我们尝试过的最时尚的电子墨水平板电脑之一。它有一个 10.3 英寸的单色数字纸显示屏，周围环绕着米色边框，最粗的部分位于底部边缘，您可以自然地握住它。左侧有一个细长的银色边框，可连接对开式保护套和新型<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/remarkable-2-type-folio-keyboard-hands-on-130057978.html">Type Folio 键盘</a>等配件。向 reMarkable 致敬，他们制造了一款电子墨水平板电脑，让您可以轻松地与所有其他精美小玩意儿搭配使用。</p><p>我们先来说一下 reMarkable 2 的写作和阅读体验，两者都很棒。从一开始，涂鸦、涂鸦和写作就变得轻而易举。我们测试了 Marker Plus，它有一个内置橡皮擦，但它和标准 Marker 都是倾斜和压力敏感笔，不需要电池或充电。我观察到，在按下 reMarkable 2 的屏幕和显示线条之间基本上没有延迟。延迟非常低，感觉最接近实际的笔和纸。但我要说的是，这在本指南中的首选中并不是独一无二的——我们测试的几乎所有电子墨水平板电脑都正确地具备了这一非常重要的功能。</p><p>在阅读方面，reMarkable 2 支持 PDF 和 ePUB，您可以通过在桌面上登录您的 reMarkable 帐户或通过手机上的配套移动应用程序将文件添加到设备。您还可以将 Google Drive、Microsoft OneDrive 或 Dropbox 帐户与 reMarkable 帐户配对，并以这种方式访问​​文件。对于那些阅读大量学术论文或审查许多工作文档的人来说，这应该足够好了。对于从 Kindle 或 Kobo 商店等在线市场购买电子书的人来说，这会更困难，但他们还有其他选择。</p><p>将文档加载到 reMarkable 2 上的另一种有趣方式是通过 Google Chrome 的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://support.remarkable.com/s/article/Read-on-reMarkable-Google-Chrome-Extension">Read with reMarkable 扩展</a>。安装它并配对您的 reMarkable 帐户后，您将能够将在线找到的文章直接发送到您的 reMarkable 2，以便您稍后查看。您甚至可以将这些文件自定义为仅作为文本发送，这样您就可以直接在 reMarkable 上更改其格式，或者作为 PDF 文件发送。无论您选择哪一个，您都可以像在 E Ink 平板电脑上标记任何其他文件一样标记这些文章。我经常使用这个扩展，而且我确实比在 iPhone 上更喜欢在 reMarkable 2 上阅读长篇文章。对我来说，能够在这些故事下划线、突出显示或以其他方式标记这些故事更多的是一种额外的好处，而不是必要的，但对于其他从在线材料中收集资源的人来说，这样做会更好。</p><p>总体而言，将文件加载到 reMarkable 2 上非常容易，并且可以访问它们<br>在其他地方，当您可能无法拿出电子墨水平板电脑时。订阅了 reMarkable Connect 的用户将获得最佳体验，而且购买后即可获得一年会员资格，这是一项不错的福利。每月 3 美元的订阅使您能够使用桌面和移动应用程序编辑现有笔记并从任何地方获取新笔记，以及无限的云存储和同步。在最后方面，如果您不支付 Connect 费用，则 reMarkable 的配套应用程序中将仅提供“过去 50 天内在线同步的笔记和文档”。我怀疑 50 天的文档同步对于某些人来说已经足够了，但对于高级用户来说就不够了。无论如何，将记笔记功能放在付费专区后面的任何地方都有点令人失望，并且使任何人都更难使用 reMarkable 生态系统作为他们的主要记笔记空间。</p><p>也就是说，我将大部分测试都放在了 reMarkable 2 本身上，并且它作为数字笔记本的能力给我留下了深刻的印象，而无需陡峭的学习曲线。您可以创建不同的笔记本和“快速工作表”来组织手写笔记，并创建文件夹来理解导入的文件。您将找到八种不同的画笔类型，用于标记文档和做笔记，以及可自定义的线条粗细和“颜色”（仅在平板电脑本身上显示为阴影）。您甚至可以在文档中的任意位置进行输入，并且 reMarkable 2 可以将手写笔记以惊人的准确性翻译成机器可读的文本。</p><p> reMarkable 2 最终拥有最佳的功能组合以及相对较低的学习曲线，这并不令人意外。该公司是早在 2017 年率先推出真正可行的电子墨水平板电脑的公司之一，从那时起他们就一直在完善这种体验。但这是有代价的——reMarkable 2 不是我们测试过的最昂贵的电子墨水平板电脑，但它也不便宜。仅平板电脑就需要 299 美元，然后您必须分别花费 79 美元或 129 美元购买 Marker 或 Marker Plus。总而言之，您可以花 430 美元购买最好的 reMarkable 2 版本（假设您跳过新的 199 美元的 Type Folio 键盘）。您可以以相同的价格购买<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDlHOUZQSFk2P3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLXN6LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1N2Y0MTQxMy1lZWMyLTRkOTAtOWMyNS0yNmQxNDRiNzM3YjgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAaHdYB0mgCPBg7zx258vdIxAr1q7PoDemtHyOyJMAgfg&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB09G9FPHY6">第 9 代 iPad</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJKTEc2OVFSP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLXN6LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1N2Y0MTQxMy1lZWMyLTRkOTAtOWMyNS0yNmQxNDRiNzM3YjgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAR3plQ35s44yAGBMzwtaGSPp_Eef95rY0Qn0HqccrW6H&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BJLG69QR">第 1 代 Apple Pencil</a> ，并且您将拥有更灵活的组合，完全基于 iOS 的功能。</p><p>但您考虑使用 iPad 的原因可能不是出于特定原因，无论是您对电子墨水的喜爱还是笔在纸上书写的感觉，或者您只是想要一种更无干扰的体验。如果您正在寻找一款无需花费很长时间就能适应的电子墨水平板电脑，它能提供一流的书写体验，并且可以相对简单地在其他地方访问笔记，那么 reMarkable 2 是您的最佳选择。</p><h2>最佳电子阅读器电子墨水平板电脑：Amazon Kindle Scribe</h2><p><core-commerce id="237e968b4db2445da9bb8effd0a5399b" data-type="product-list"></p><p>在这个领域你确实有两个选择： <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdC0Fw-hbXTKxeT98YDCPi9hN-D3BUxUadt7VDXv3ZKD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FIntroducing-Kindle-Scribe-the-first-Kindle-for-reading-and-writing%2Fdp%2FB09BRZBK15%3Fth%3D1">Amazon Kindle Scribe</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3VzLmtvYm9ib29rcy5jb20vY29sbGVjdGlvbnMvZXJlYWRlcnMvcHJvZHVjdHMva29iby1lbGlwc2EtMmUiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjU3ZjQxNDEzLWVlYzItNGQ5MC05YzI1LTI2ZDE0NGI3MzdiOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAeZveHuXrK0VMeYhNin7_ql2ZevRFNROg2Anfxn_pw2H&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fus.kobobooks.com%2Fcollections%2Fereaders%2Fproducts%2Fkobo-elipsa-2e">Kobo Elipsa 2E</a> 。 Scribe 击败 Elipsa 2E 纯粹是因为其低延迟的笔和屏幕组合。 Elipsa 有其优点，我们稍后会详细介绍，但在无缝、流畅的手写体验方面，它无法与 Scribe 竞争。</p><p>我们已经对 Kindle Scribe 进行了<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-kindle-scribe-review-e-ink-reader-tablet-pen-drawing-price-battery-life-140019784.html">全面的评测</a>，总的来说，我在本指南的测试过程中也很享受它。如前所述，使用配套笔在 Scribe 上书写时几乎没有延迟。由于<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kindle-scribe-update-adds-new-brushes-and-better-organization-210011764.html">最新的软件更新</a>，您现在还有更多画笔类型可供选择，包括钢笔、记号笔和铅笔，这增添了魅力。与其他电子墨水平板电脑一样，Scribe 可以轻松创建多个笔记本，如果您愿意，您可以向它们添加页面并更改其模板。</p><p>作为一款电子阅读器，Scribe 的出色之处不仅在于其 10.2 英寸显示屏和自动调节前灯，还因为您触手可及的亚马逊整个电子书商店。如果您从 Amazon 获取大部分阅读材料或订阅<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAARj6eFOV3M9G1Z8l-1D34ToGloYCJ9BXtTXTUuTYEf76&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fkindle-dbs%2Fhz%2Fsubscribe%2Fku%3FshoppingPortalEnabled%3Dtrue">Kindle Unlimited</a> ，您将能够在 Scribe 上立即跳转到您的所有图书。此外，Scribe 还可以通过蓝牙连接到 Audible。从当地图书馆获取电子书并在 Kindle 上阅读也很容易。这不仅对于贪婪的读者来说至关重要，对于购买或租用数字教科书的学生以及经常出于研究目的而阅读书籍的学生来说尤其如此。</p><p>在使用 Scribe 时，我经常为学生着想。我于 2009 年开始上大学，即第一台 Kindle 发布两年后，第一台 iPad 发布前一年。对我来说，获取数字教科书确实不是一个选择，但我可以理解像 Kindle Scribe 这样的笔记设备对学生的吸引力。它可以说比标准的 Kindle 更好，因为它的屏幕尺寸更大，这会让长时间盯着看不那么累。在学习时添加手写笔记的功能是锦上添花。</p><p> However, Amazon&#39;s execution of book notes is not my favorite. You actually cannot take notes in the margins of Kindle ebooks. Instead you press and hold the pen&#39;s tip on the screen to highlight text or add a note to a particular word or phrase. If you do the latter, a window pops up on the bottom half of the screen where you can either take a handwritten note or type a text note using the Scribe&#39;s mildly frustrating and sluggish on-screen keyboard.</p><p> Amazon recently rectified this a bit with a <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-kindle-scribe-updates-include-support-for-direct-on-page-writing-051753157.html">software update</a> that allows for direct on-page writing in certain Kindle books. The Kindle Store now has a section that showcases &quot;Write-on Books,&quot; which is currently mostly made up of journals and game books that feature puzzles like crosswords and sudoku. This is certainly a step in the right direction, but it means you still won&#39;t be able to mark up your favorite fiction and non-fiction books until they support the new feature.</p><p> This is where I give a nod to the <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3VzLmtvYm9ib29rcy5jb20vY29sbGVjdGlvbnMvZXJlYWRlcnMvcHJvZHVjdHMva29iby1lbGlwc2EtMmUiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjU3ZjQxNDEzLWVlYzItNGQ5MC05YzI1LTI2ZDE0NGI3MzdiOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAeZveHuXrK0VMeYhNin7_ql2ZevRFNROg2Anfxn_pw2H&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fus.kobobooks.com%2Fcollections%2Fereaders%2Fproducts%2Fkobo-elipsa-2e">Kobo Elipsa 2E</a> , where you <em>can</em> write notes in the margins, underline, circle and otherwise mark up your reading material. It&#39;s a more natural (and fun) experience since it mimics what you&#39;d do if you were reading a physical book. It&#39;s a shame that the latency on the <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/kobo-takes-on-the-kindle-scribe-with-improved-elipsa-2e-e-ink-tablet-040148388.html">Elipsa</a> was just a hair more noticeable than that of the Scribe. If it weren&#39;t for that, it might have beaten Amazon&#39;s device here.</p><p> What that extra bit of latency translates to in practice is handwriting that can come out just a bit messier, and that increases precipitously the faster you write. But that also means that you&#39;ll notice this the most when taking notes longhand on the Elipsa; if you&#39;re primarily using an E Ink tablet to mark up documents, it won&#39;t affect you as much. Despite that, I did like the way Kobo executed notebooks on the Elipsa. You can have a standard notebook where you can write and scribble away, or an “advanced” notebook that supports handwriting-to-text conversion and inserting things like diagrams and formulas. Text conversion is actually pretty accurate, too, even when dealing with some of my ugliest handwriting.</p><p> Kobo also has a pretty sizable ebook marketplace, so it&#39;s certainly a decent option if you want to stay clear of the Amazon ecosystem. But Amazon has the upper hand when it comes to price. The Kobo Elipsa 2E pack that includes its stylus is $399, while the 16GB Kindle Scribe with the premium pen (which includes dedicated eraser and shortcut buttons) comes in at $369. Even if you max out the Scribe with 64GB of storage, you&#39;d only spend $20 more than you would on the Kobo Elipsa. That, combined with the Scribe&#39;s strong overall performance and the ubiquity of Amazon&#39;s ebook offerings will make it the better choice for most readers.</p><h2> Best E Ink tablet for note-taking: Supernote X</h2><p><core-commerce id="c288fe0a90d747d2986f7e88442f9644" data-type="product-list"></p><p> I spent a while testing all of these E Ink tablets, and the <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://supernote.com/collections/devices/products/supernote">Supernote X</a> is the one I was consistently most excited to use. As a notebook nerd, I find this thing so cool. Available in 10.3-inch (what I tested) and 7.8-inch sizes, the Supernote X has a “FeelWrite” screen protector that has a different feel than a standard E Ink screen. When writing on it with Heart of Metal Pen 2, which is weighty and looks like a fountain pen, you get a gel pen-like feel rather than the subtly scratchy vibe that other E Ink tablets have. In fact, the Supernote X has one of the best writing experiences out of any tablet I tested.</p><p> The Supernote X supports a range of file formats, including PDF, ePUB, Word (.doc), PNG and JPG, which really opens up the content you can put onto the thing. I wanted to see if I could treat it almost like a digital bullet journal, and that wasn&#39;t hard to do. There are built-in page templates, but I was able to download daily, weekly and monthly planner templates online, resize them and move them onto the Supernote X using <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.android.com/filetransfer/">Android File Transfer</a> . The device has a dedicated “MyStyle” folder where you can save files you want to use as templates. The most difficult part was making sure I had the dimensions right while resizing the documents. Once saved in the right folder, I could make an entire notebook out of the templates I had gotten from the internet for free.</p><p> Supernote does have its own “app store,” but there&#39;s not much in there, and its Play Store offerings are limited to only the Kindle app. This device doesn&#39;t have a backlight, so it won&#39;t be easy to see in dark environments. But you can download Amazon&#39;s ebook app and read just like you would on a standard tablet (no, you can&#39;t mark up books here either).</p><p> Honestly, the last thing I wanted to do with the Supernote X was read, though. The device really shines as an E Ink notebook and the company clearly put a lot of thought into “building a better mousetrap,” so to speak. You can translate handwritten words into typed text, but you don&#39;t have to do that in order for the software to recognize your handwriting. There&#39;s a keywords feature that lets you basically bookmark important phrases for quick access later. All you need to do is lasso the word, press the keyword button and the tablet&#39;s software will translate your writing into typed text. Then you can add it as a keyword and quickly jump back to it from the left-side tablet of contents menu. Similarly, you can bookmark titles and add stars to pages that are important, all of which help you jump between important bits.</p><p> That said, the Supernote X sometimes felt a little inconsistent. The writing experience was top-notch, but there were other things that felt a little less polished. For example, you can swipe down on the right bezel to bring up a menu that lets you quickly navigate between favorited notes and recent documents – that&#39;s quite thoughtful. But then the Files page just has a couple of starkly named folders like Export, Screenshot and Inbox that I didn&#39;t touch once, and the pen sidebar has more options than most people will know what to do with (and none of them have text labels).</p><p> These are small nit-picks, but they go to show that the Supernote X might not be the best device for tech novices. There is a learning curve here, but notebook nerds like myself will be thrilled with all that the Supernote X has to offer. Unsurprisingly, all those advanced features come at a steep price: the A5-sized tablet with a folio and pen will set you back at least $532, making it the most expensive set on our list.</p><h2> Honorable mention: Boox Note Air 2 Plus</h2><p><core-commerce id="cfaf0b0dd1d44eb0845bc396b8025295" data-type="product-list"></p><p> If you removed some of the notebook-specific features from the Supernote X and added in a more complete version of Android 11, you&#39;d get the <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3Nob3AuYm9veC5jb20vcHJvZHVjdHMvbm90ZWFpcjIiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjU3ZjQxNDEzLWVlYzItNGQ5MC05YzI1LTI2ZDE0NGI3MzdiOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAdei88kTG0OgbrsP-ZrtuPt--mNsHKxhysGtwxbE3u5z&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fshop.boox.com%2Fproducts%2Fnoteair2">Boox Note Air 2 Plus</a> . Boox makes a number of interesting E Ink devices and the Note Air 2 Plus is the one that best compares to the others on our list thanks to its 10.3-inch display. This is an E Ink Android tablet, so that means you can actually download Android apps like Kindle, Kobo and others. There&#39;s even a web browser, and yes, you can watch videos on this thing, too.</p><p> Of course, just because you can do all of that doesn&#39;t mean you should. E Ink screens are truly best for reading and writing, so I didn&#39;t spend much time binge watching YouTube on the Note Air 2 Plus – but I was happy that I had the freedom to do so. Really, the utility of Android comes in with the app store and I expect that most people will use it to download all of their favorite reading and writing apps. Much like a standard tablet, the Note Air 2 Plus will be a great option for anyone that gets their reading material from a bunch of different places — and since you can manually transfer documents from your computer to the device, too, it&#39;s far-and-away the most versatile option on our list.</p><p> I experienced little to no latency when writing on the Note Air 2 Plus and I was happy with the number of brush options it has. Like the Supernote X, it comes with a bunch of page templates you can use, or you can bring in your own PDFs and other documents to use as templates. There&#39;s an “AI recognition” feature that translates a whole page&#39;s handwriting into typed text, and it&#39;s actually pretty accurate. (Though, it did consistently confuse my “&amp;” for a capital A). I also appreciated that you can add other kinds of material to your notes, including web pages and voice recordings, and share notes as PDFs or PNGs via email, Google Drive and other services. Features like those ensure that, with this partially analog device, you don&#39;t miss out on some of the conveniences that a true digital notebook system would have.</p><p> Instead of going into all of the features the Note Air 2 Plus offers, I think it&#39;s most useful to talk about the value of this device. A bundle with the tablet, a standard pen and a folio case comes in at $500, putting it on the higher end of the price spectrum among the devices we tested. But considering it&#39;s a full Android tablet, that doesn&#39;t seem absurd. Those who want to avoid distractions most of the time while still having access to email and a web browser might gravitate towards a device like this. Also, most of Boox&#39;s devices operate in the same way, so you do have more affordable options if you like this blueprint. For example, the <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3Nob3AuYm9veC5jb20vcHJvZHVjdHMvbm92YWFpcjIiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjU3ZjQxNDEzLWVlYzItNGQ5MC05YzI1LTI2ZDE0NGI3MzdiOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAfSLLBauv6iap2X84U4Z0Qe4-8_v9LefC7xeba2sFs_R&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fshop.boox.com%2Fproducts%2Fnovaair2">Boox Nova Air 2</a> is a 7.8-inch version of the Note Air 2 Plus, with slightly different RAM and storage specs to match, and its bundle comes in at $370.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-e-ink-tablet-130037939.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-e-ink-tablet-130037939.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 57f41413-eec2-4d90-9c25-26d144b737b8</guid><dc:creator> Valentina Palladino</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 24 Jul 2023 15:00:08 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690210808</ingested><modified> 2023-07-24T15:00:30+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Valentina Palladino]]></category><media:content height="1050" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/419ffb10-ddeb-11ed-bff9-d85a10e367ae" width="1587"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1050" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/419ffb10-ddeb-11ed-bff9-d85a10e367ae" width="1587"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Valentina Palladino]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Five E ink tablets laying with their screens up on a beige carpet.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[E-ink tablets]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Shark robot vacuums are up to 45 percent off on Amazon]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Shark makes some of the best robot vacuum cleaners around a